codex
I’ve identified a concrete parser weakness in this lane: when a U.S.C. section marker is isolated as its own segment (e.g., `§3110.`), fallback can emit a frame formula with an empty/weak predicate (`unnamed_predicate` or a single letter).  

I’m implementing one generalized deterministic rule in `legal_modal_parser`:
1. If a section-heading fallback candidate is mostly just the section reference, try to merge it with the immediate heading-like neighbor segment.
2. Keep this merge narrow: only for U.S.C. heading fallback, only when token-poor, and only when the neighbor still looks like a heading (no verb-heavy clause).
3. Add a regression test fixture for the three packet citations (`42 U.S.C. 1395w`, `5 U.S.C. 3110`, `16 U.S.C. 2204`) asserting non-empty deterministic fallback with meaningful predicate tokens.
4. Run the smallest relevant modal codec/parser tests.
